  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat the oven to 200°C. Place the chicken into a bowl. Add the lemongrass, ginger, red chilli, garlic, sugar, soy, balsamic vinegar, and water into a blender. Blend until smooth. Taste and season with salt and pepper, if needed, and pour over the chicken. Toss together."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Transfer the marinated chicken onto an oiled baking tray, pouring over all of the marinade. Slide into the oven for 20-25 mins, until cooked through. Check half way through and add a splash of water if the marinade is caramelising too quickly."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the rainbow salad, use a peeler to shred the red cabbage and slice the carrots into thin matchsticks. Pick the mint leaves, discarding the stems, then combine the veg and herbs with the juice of a lime. Season to taste with salt and some sugar. Crush your peanuts."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Reheat the rice and serve onto plates. Slice the chicken and place on top with some rainbow salad. Finish with a sprinkling of crushed peanuts."
    }
  ],
